longBusinessSummary: Sayona Mining Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the identification, acquisition, evaluation, and exploration of mineral assets in Australia and Canada. It primarily explores for lithium and graphite. The company's flagship project is the Authier Lithium Project located in Quebec, Canada. It also holds interest in the Tansim project with 275 claims covering 15,907 hectares of prospective lithium acreage located in Quebec. The company was formerly known as DiamonEx Limited and changed its name to Sayona Mining Limited in May 2013. Sayona Mining Limited was incorporated in 2000 and is headquartered in Paddington, Australia.
